Sokoto State Governor Aminu Waziri Tambuwal has signed the 2020 Appropriation Bill of N202 billion into law. He commended the house of assembly for its speedy consideration of the budget in three weeks in line with the World Bank benchmark. Governor Tambuwal stated this while granting assent to the Bill at the Council Chamber of Government House, Sokoto. He noted: “The Assembly despite being controlled by the APC which is in the majority has rallied round the government and supported it in the interest of serving the people of the state.” Tambuwal added: “Members of Sokoto House of Assembly must be commended for their uncommon patriotism to deliver democratic dividends to the people of Sokoto State.” This gesture, he declared “shall not be misplaced.” He assured that the Executive would work closely with the legislature to ensure proper implementation of the budget. According to him, the crux of their commitment supersedes party affiliations. Speaker of the Sokoto State House of Assembly, Aminu Muhammad Achida, assured: “We will continue to accelerate the passage of any bill that is meant to improve the lots of the people of the state.” Achida pointed out that the implementation of the 2019 budget recorded a lot in the areas of education, health and rural development among others. He acknowledged the success recorded by the Executive in the improvement of Internally Generated Revenue (IGR).  Tambuwal signs Sokoto's 2020 budget of N202bn Sokoto State''s 2016 budget will reflect yearnings, aspirations of the people -Tambuwal Sokoto State''s 2016 budget will reflect yearnings, aspirations of the people -Tambuwal